'''Ōkunitama Shrine / Ōkunitama Shrine''' (おおくにたまじんじゃ) is the name used for certain Shinto shrines, rendered either as "大国魂神社" or "大國魂神社", and also sometimes written as "大国霊神社" or "大国玉神社". Below is an explanation of the differences in the kanji spellings followed by a list of the major shrines under each spelling.
== Spelled as "大国魂神社" == This form uses the simplified character {{ill|国|ja|国|12=draft}} in place of the traditional {{ill|國|ja|國|12=draft}}. It is the form commonly used in modern contexts. * {{ill|Aizu Ōkunitama Shrine|ja|会津大国魂神社|12=draft}} – located in {{ill|Fukushima Prefecture|ja|福島県|12=draft}}, {{ill|Ōnuma District|ja|大沼郡|12=draft}}, {{ill|Aizumisato Town|ja|会津美里町|12=draft}}, Miyabayashi: a subsidiary shrine within the precincts of {{ill|Isasumi Shrine|ja|伊佐須美神社|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Ōkunitama Shrine (Sakai City, Sakai Ward)|ja|大国魂神社 (堺市堺区)|12=draft}} – located in {{ill|Osaka Prefecture|ja|大阪府|12=draft}}, {{ill|Sakai City|ja|堺市|12=draft}}, {{ill|Sakai Ward|ja|堺区|12=draft}}, {{ill|Kaimachi-higashi|ja|甲斐町東|12=draft}}: a subsidiary shrine within the precincts of {{ill|Kaikou Shrine|ja|開口神社|12=draft}}.
=== Branches of [[Ōyamato Shrine]] === * {{ill|Yamato Okunitama Shrine, Minamiawaji|ja|大和大国魂神社|12=draft}} – located in {{ill|Hyōgo Prefecture|ja|兵庫県|12=draft}}, {{ill|Minamiawaji City|ja|南あわじ市|12=draft}}, Enokiretsu. * {{ill|Yamato Okunitama Shrine, Mima|ja|倭大国魂神社|12=draft}} – located in {{ill|Tokushima Prefecture|ja|徳島県|12=draft}}, {{ill|Mima City|ja|美馬市|12=draft}}, {{ill|Mimamachi|ja|美馬町|12=draft}}, Shigekiyo.
