'''Ōkunitama Shrine / Ōkunitama Shrine''' (おおくにたまじんじゃ) is the name used for certain Shinto shrines, rendered either as "大国魂神社" or "大國魂神社", and also sometimes written as "大国霊神社" or "大国玉神社". Below is an explanation of the differences in the kanji spellings followed by a list of the major shrines under each spelling.
== Spelled as "大国魂神社" == This form uses the simplified character {{ill|国|ja|国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/国|qq=}} in place of the traditional {{ill|國|ja|國|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/國|qq=}}. It is the form commonly used in modern contexts. * {{ill|Aizu Ōkunitama Shrine|ja|会津大国魂神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Aizu Ōkunitama Shrine|qq=}} – located in {{ill|Fukushima Prefecture|ja|福島県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fukushima Prefecture|qq=}}, {{ill|Ōnuma District|ja|大沼郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōnuma District|qq=}}, {{ill|Aizumisato Town|ja|Aizumisato|1=Aizumisato|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Aizumisato Town|13=User:Immanuelle/Aizumisato|qq=}}, Miyabayashi: a subsidiary shrine within the precincts of {{ill|Isasumi Shrine|ja|伊佐須美神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Isasumi Shrine|qq=}}. * {{ill|Ōkunitama Shrine (Sakai City, Sakai Ward)|ja|大国魂神社 (堺市堺区)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkunitama Shrine (Sakai City, Sakai Ward)|qq=}} – located in {{ill|Osaka Prefecture|ja|大阪府|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Osaka Prefecture|qq=}}, {{ill|Sakai City|ja|堺市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sakai City|qq=}}, {{ill|Sakai Ward|ja|堺区|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sakai Ward|qq=}}, {{ill|Kaimachi-higashi|ja|甲斐町東|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kaimachi-higashi|qq=}}: a subsidiary shrine within the precincts of {{ill|Kaikou Shrine|ja|開口神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kaikou Shrine|qq=}}.
=== Branches of [[Ōyamato Shrine]] === * {{ill|Yamato Okunitama Shrine, Minamiawaji|ja|大和大国魂神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamato Okunitama Shrine, Minamiawaji|qq=}} – located in {{ill|Hyōgo Prefecture|ja|兵庫県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hyōgo Prefecture|qq=}}, {{ill|Minamiawaji City|ja|南あわじ市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minamiawaji City|qq=}}, Enokiretsu. * {{ill|Yamato Okunitama Shrine, Mima|ja|倭大国魂神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamato Okunitama Shrine, Mima|qq=}} – located in {{ill|Tokushima Prefecture|ja|徳島県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokushima Prefecture|qq=}}, {{ill|Mima City|ja|美馬市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mima City|qq=}}, {{ill|Mimamachi|ja|美馬町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mimamachi|qq=}}, Shigekiyo.
== Spelled as "大國魂神社" == This form retains the traditional character {{ill|國|ja|國|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/國|qq=}} and is often used by shrines that emphasize historical prestige or formality. * {{ill|Ōkunitama Shrine (Iwaki)|ja|大國魂神社 (いわき市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkunitama Shrine (Iwaki)|qq=}} – located in {{ill|Fukushima Prefecture|ja|福島県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fukushima Prefecture|qq=}}, {{ill|Iwaki City|ja|いわき市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iwaki City|qq=}}, Hirasuganami. * {{ill|Ōkunitama Shrine|ja|大國魂神社|1=Ōkunitama Shrine|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkunitama Shrine|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkunitama Shrine|qq=}} – located in {{ill|Tokyo Metropolis|ja|東京都|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokyo Metropolis|qq=}}, {{ill|Fuchū City|ja|府中市 (東京都)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fuchū City|qq=}}, {{ill|Miyamachi|ja|宮町 (東京都府中市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miyamachi|qq=}}: the head shrine (総社) of {{ill|Musashi Province|ja|武蔵国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Musashi Province|qq=}}, hosting the annual grand festival {{ill|Kurayami Festival|ja|くらやみ祭|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kurayami Festival|qq=}}. * {{ill|Shima Ōkunitama Shrine|ja|島大國魂神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shima Ōkunitama Shrine|qq=}} – located in {{ill|Nagasaki Prefecture|ja|長崎県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagasaki Prefecture|qq=}}, {{ill|Tsushima City|ja|対馬市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsushima City|qq=}}, Kamitsushima Town.
== Spelled as "大国霊神社" == This variant uses the character {{ill|霊|ja|霊|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/霊|qq=}} (rei) instead of {{ill|魂|ja|魂|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/魂|qq=}} (tama). The reading may be "Ōkunitama Jinja" or "Ōkunirei Jinja". * {{ill|Owari Ōkunitama Shrine|ja|尾張大国霊神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Owari Ōkunitama Shrine|qq=}} – located in {{ill|Aichi Prefecture|ja|愛知県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Aichi Prefecture|qq=}}, {{ill|Inazawa City|ja|稲沢市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Inazawa City|qq=}}, {{ill|Kokufumiya Shrine|ja|国府宮 (稲沢市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kokufumiya Shrine|qq=}}: also known as Kokufumiya Shrine.
== Spelled as "大国玉神社" == This variant employs the character {{ill|玉|ja|玉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/玉|qq=}} (tama) to denote sacred treasures. It is usually rendered in the simplified form "大国玉神社", though in some cases the traditional form "大國玉神社" is used. * {{ill|Ōkunitama Shrine (Sakuragawa)|ja|大国玉神社 (桜川市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkunitama Shrine (Sakuragawa)|qq=}} – located in {{ill|Ibaraki Prefecture|ja|茨城県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ibaraki Prefecture|qq=}}, {{ill|Sakuragawa City|ja|桜川市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sakuragawa City|qq=}}, Ogunitama: also referred to as 大國玉神社. * {{ill|Ōkunitama Shrine (Matsusaka)|ja|大国玉神社 (松阪市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkunitama Shrine (Matsusaka)|qq=}} – located in {{ill|Mie Prefecture|ja|三重県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mie Prefecture|qq=}}, {{ill|Matsusaka City|ja|松阪市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsusaka City|qq=}}, Rokkon Town. * {{ill|Ōkunitama Shrine (Iki)|ja|大國玉神社 (壱岐市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkunitama Shrine (Iki)|qq=}} – located in {{ill|Nagasaki Prefecture|ja|長崎県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagasaki Prefecture|qq=}}, {{ill|Iki City|ja|壱岐市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iki City|qq=}}, Gounoura Town.
== Related Topics == * {{ill|Kunitama|ja|国魂|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kunitama|qq=}}
