== Spelled as "大国玉神社" == This variant employs the character {{ill|玉|ja|玉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/玉|qq=}} (tama) to denote sacred treasures. It is usually rendered in the simplified form "大国玉神社", though in some cases the traditional form "大國玉神社" is used. * {{ill|Ōkunitama Shrine (Sakuragawa)|ja|大国玉神社 (桜川市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkunitama Shrine (Sakuragawa)|qq=}} – located in {{ill|Ibaraki Prefecture|ja|茨城県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ibaraki Prefecture|qq=}}, {{ill|Sakuragawa City|ja|桜川市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sakuragawa City|qq=}}, Ogunitama: also referred to as 大國玉神社. * {{ill|Ōkunitama Shrine (Matsusaka)|ja|大国玉神社 (松阪市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkunitama Shrine (Matsusaka)|qq=}} – located in {{ill|Mie Prefecture|ja|三重県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mie Prefecture|qq=}}, {{ill|Matsusaka City|ja|松阪市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsusaka City|qq=}}, Rokkon Town. * {{ill|Ōkunitama Shrine (Iki)|ja|大國玉神社 (壱岐市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkunitama Shrine (Iki)|qq=}} – located in {{ill|Nagasaki Prefecture|ja|長崎県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagasaki Prefecture|qq=}}, {{ill|Iki City|ja|壱岐市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iki City|qq=}}, Gounoura Town.
